    "text": "Mount Everest (8,848.86m / 29,031.7ft) is Earth's highest mountain above sea level, on the Nepal-Tibet (China) border. First ascent: Edmund Hillary and Tenzing Norgay (May 29, 1953). Over 6,000 people have summited; ~330 have died trying. Commercial expeditions (1990s+) dramatically increased summit attempts.",
